body:
Adds `--cache` argument to cython command. It is built on top of #6090 and should be merged after it.

~~I suppose additional tests are needed to this PR. I will try to add to this PR.~~

Tests added. 

Related to #6070

comment_data.body: Not sure whether this TestCyCache module should not be placed somewhere else since it is not related to Build package only anymore...
This change is causing test_grammar.py tests failing. Not sure what is best to do here. Should be compile_single extended to support cache (context creation needs to be added then)?

-        if not options.timestamps:

comment_data.body: Or cache module will be moved to `Build` directory - see: https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/6090#discussion_r1527455984
Now when `Cache.py` is in `Build`directory this comment is not valid anymore I think...

> `'c++' if options.cplus else None`

I'd rather use `'c'` explicitly here instead of `None`. In any case, this should be normalised for both usages, not just here.

comment_data.body: Shouldn't the caching happen *after* the out of date check?
The cache is persistent, so it shouldn't depend on the number of modules that users compile whether it's being used or not.

commit.message: Move Cython cache to separate module

Apply suggestions from code review

Co-authored-by: da-woods <dw-git@d-woods.co.uk>
Add compilation cache to cython command
Use Cache module from Cython.Build package
